From 9dc08868d8a4c4c65586388b3e3c57b90690f1ba Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Thu, 2 Apr 2026 13:52:49 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 067/174] LoongArch: fix stack_top() VDSO size alignment for
 PGCL

stack_top() used PAGE_ALIGN() for the VDSO size, but the VDSO
is mapped at MMUPAGE granularity.  With PGCL (PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4),
PAGE_ALIGN rounds a 16KB VDSO up to 256KB, wasting 240KB of
virtual address space below the stack.

Use MMUPAGE_ALIGN() to match the actual VDSO mapping granularity.

Signed-off-by: William Irwin <wli@holomorphy.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/loongarch/kernel/process.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/loongarch/kernel/process.c b/arch/loongarch/kernel/process.c
index 375220dfeca9..7a7a7cc57f71 100644
--- a/arch/loongarch/kernel/process.c
+++ b/arch/loongarch/kernel/process.c
@@ -324,7 +324,7 @@ unsigned long stack_top(void)
 
 	if (current->thread.vdso) {
 		/* Space for the VDSO & data page */
-		top -= PAGE_ALIGN(current->thread.vdso->size);
+		top -= MMUPAGE_ALIGN(current->thread.vdso->size);
 		top -= VVAR_SIZE;
 
 		/* Space to randomize the VDSO base */
